\f[CR]/usr/share/pepc/tests/emul\-data\f[R]
.RE
.TP
\f[B]\-\-force\-color\f[R]
Force colorized output even if the output stream is not a terminal (adds
ANSI escape codes).
.TP
\f[B]\-\-print\-man\-path\f[R]
Print the pepc manual pages directory path and exit.
Add this path to the \f[CR]MANPATH\f[R] environment variable to make the
manual pages available to the \[aq]man\[aq] tool.
.SS Subcommand \f[I]\[aq]info\[aq]\f[R]
Retrieve PCI ASPM information for the system.
.TP
\f[B]\-\-policy\f[R]
Retrieve the current global PCI ASPM policy from
\f[CR]/sys/module/pcie_aspm/parameters/policy\f[R].
The \[dq]default\[dq] policy indicates the system\[aq]s default.
.TP
\f[B]\-\-policies\f[R]
Retrieve the list of available PCI ASPM policies from
\f[CR]/sys/module/pcie_aspm/parameters/policy\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]\-\-device\f[R] \f[I]ADDR\f[R]
Specify the PCI device address for the \[aq]\-\-l1\-aspm\[aq] option.
Example: \[aq]0000:00:02.0\[aq].
.TP
\f[B]\-\-l1\-aspm\f[R]
Retrieve the L1 ASPM status (on/off) for the PCI device specified by
\[aq]\-\-device\[aq].
Reads from \f[CR]/sys/bus/pci/devices/{device}/link/l1_aspm\f[R].
.SS Subcommand \f[I]\[aq]config\[aq]\f[R]
Configure PCI ASPM settings.
If no parameter is provided, the current value(s) will be displayed.
.TP
\f[B]\-\-policy\f[R] \f[I][POLICY]\f[R]
Set the global PCI ASPM policy by writing to
\f[CR]/sys/module/pcie_aspm/parameters/policy\f[R].
Use \[dq]default\[dq] to reset the policy to the system\[aq]s default
setting.
.TP
\f[B]\-\-device\f[R] \f[I]ADDR\f[R]
Specify the PCI device address for the \[aq]\-\-l1\-aspm\[aq] option.
Example: \[aq]0000:00:02.0\[aq].
.TP
\f[B]\-\-l1\-aspm\f[R] \f[I][OPTION]\f[R]
Enable or disable L1 ASPM for the PCI device specified by
\[aq]\-\-device\[aq].
This is done via \f[CR]/sys/bus/pci/devices/{device}/link/l1_aspm\f[R].
Valid values are \[aq]on\[aq], \[aq]off\[aq], \[aq]enable\[aq],
\[aq]disable\[aq], \[aq]true\[aq], or \[aq]false\[aq].
